doc.after: Order Suliformes Family Phalacrocoracidae Cormorants are medium to large aquatic birds usually with mainly dark plumage and areas of colored skin on the face The bill is long thin and sharply hooked Their feet are four toed and webbed a distinguishing feature among the Pelecaniformes order
